<subSubSection id="C0C5B0BF5A31FF9F17FAFDF5FEF2FCFC" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8860E3345A31FF9F17FAFDF5FEF2FCFC" blockId="16.[151,1437,474,1599]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F17FAFDF5FECDFD66" bold="true" box="[199,314,618,643]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F1677FDF5FDF4FD66" box="[330,515,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">Dorsal forewing</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F1528FDF5FDD1FD66" bold="true" box="[533,550,618,643]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">lf</emphasis>
short, without clear marked borders; 
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F14E7FDF5FC1AFD66" bold="true" box="[986,1005,618,643]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">tf</emphasis>
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F14D0FDE6FC02FD62" bold="true" box="[1005,1013,633,647]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">2</emphasis>
short and faded, almost restricted to costal margin; 
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F167CFD0EFEA3FD4F" bold="true" box="[321,340,657,682]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">tf</emphasis>
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F1669FD3FFEABFD4B" bold="true" box="[340,348,672,686]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">3</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F16ABFD0EFE5EFD4F" bold="true" box="[406,425,657,682]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">tf</emphasis>
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F1695FD3FFE47FD4B" bold="true" box="[424,432,672,686]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">4</emphasis>
distinct from each other, crossing the wing entirely; absence of 
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F13A9FD0EFB5AFD4F" bold="true" box="[1172,1197,657,682]" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">as</emphasis>
; presence of a small group of pale yellow scales, forming an additional, weakly defined blotch close to inner margin in region I. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4FDF98B75A31FF9F1646FD42FDFCFD10" authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1974" box="[379,523,732,757]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Phyllocnistis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="317" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meliacella">
<emphasis id="BAAB3F265A31FF9F1646FD42FDFCFD10" box="[379,523,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="317">P. meliacella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from which in addition to the above listed differences differs by having a longer aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
